<Response>None<//Response><time>1584646998822<//time><gmap_id>0x80dd2fd8cb91bcfd:0x698a9c4aae98ae84< /gmap_id><Rating>5<//Rating>< user>
100657272814632770333</user>
< Review>
When I need pet supplies, this is my go-to location.

I usually come here for fish supplies. This store seens to have a consistently wide array of bettas in good condition. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable, and in the past I was able to ask some questions and build my confidence as a novice fish keeper before the dawn of all the online groups. It isn't the largest fish section, but I consider it one of the best.

They always offer to help and seem to know their stuff. Not all retailers have educated employees, so it is great to know that these folks try to be familiar with animal care. The asoption events seem well organized, and the dogs visiting for training classes (or doggy daycare?) all seem happy when I pass by. If the standards of the fish secrion are upheld throughout the store (I am sure it is), this is a fantastic shop.< /Review>
< name>
Siobhan Armstrong<//name>

Today was my third time eating at Sunflower 2.  I'll definitely be back.

<resp>None</resp>< review>
Originally had a reservation for at a hotel in Palo Alto where I had stayed before.  It had substantially deteriorated in the 7 intervening years since I was there.  I was not going to spend the second night at that place.  Found the Enchante Hotel on line and booked it on Expedia.  Really nice hotel.  A little more expensive than the first hotel I was at, but it was not out of range for Silicon Valley hotels.  Attractive, newer property.  I understand the owner lives on site and her pride in the hotel shows through.  The complimentary charcuterie and cheese plate and wine during the afternoon was quite nice, as was the selection of breakfast items.  Only a couple of minor negatives: be careful on the bathroom floors.  Marble floors are attractive but slick when wet!  Also, watch your shins, because the metal bed frames are unforgiving.  But I would definitely stay there again.  I hope I have the opportunity to do so.< /review>

Stayed 6 nights here. Staff is really friendly, and the complementary breakfast is made to order and undoubtedly the best complementary breakfast experiences I've experienced to date. Note that you will be doing street parking, which has a 2 to 3 hour limit during the hours of 8/9am - 6pm, but the hotel will provide all-day passes if requested. Overall a great stay!</Review>

< name>
Graham Trummell< /name>
< Text>
Enchante is my new go-to romantic getaway hotel!  I've stayed there twice now, and I have to say that their fantastic staff is matched by a truly charming and comfortable facility.  We are welcomed with a smile any time of day or night (along with our pets, whom they have considered as well).  Each room at Enchante is themed: Apothique, Marie Antoinette, and Amerique are a few.  Guests are treated to a complimentary charcuterie plate in the evening, and a breakfast each morning.  When I made a booking error, the staff bent over backwards to accommodate me for an additional night... for which I will be eternally grateful!

Whether you're in town for business or just a vacation in the South Bay/South Peninsula, Enchante is a worthy choice.  Downtown Los Altos is just steps away, with so many choices for food and entertainment that you would never need to stray far.  Cupertino is home to one of the largest Taiwanese communities outside Taiwan so it's an excellent base camp if you're looking for a weekend of comfort food.

Parking can be tricky on busy weekends, and the occasional Street Festival blocks off the road - so be sure to check with the hotel before parking your car for the night.</Text>

<Name>Chris Cooper</Name><Review>I recently attended the 30th Anniversary event at the Remington Club Healthcare Center as a vendor (photographer).    The event was well organized and prepared, with lots of people attending.   Everyone from residents, to visitors, to the staff were all smiling and having a good time.  And how could you not have a good time, there was lots of food, music,  entertainment, games, and even recognition awards from the facility director to the residents.   Staff was kept busy answering questions, meeting and greeting folks and just making themselves available to anyone who had a question or needed anything.   Even the wait staff were always checking on me to see if there was anything I needed...and they were very busy moving about as quickly as humanly possible ensuring everyone was taken care of.   My hat is off to all involved in putting this extravaganza together.

I also had the opportunity to visit with the administrative staff and received brief tour of the facility by the lovely and friendly Admissions Coordinator, Pamela Cooper or just "Cooper" as I am told.   I also took the time to speak with some of the residents at the event and there was not a single unhappy face or negative comment from them.   From what I can gather this is a top notch facility and years down the road, should the need arise, this is where I would be happy to hang my hat and call home as many others have done.   It is a warm and friendly facility with an amazing staff who genuinely care about you.<//Review></record>

<user>109097273464006973772<//user>< username>
Kent Panter</username>
<time>1564163307543<//time><Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
After having gotten up to go pee, at 4:30 in the morning I sustained a fall.  As a result of this fall, I broke the largest bone in my body - the upper leg bone (femur). To fix it, they inserted a rod in the middle of the bone from my hip down to my knee. Then they put a nail through the rod and up in my pelvis. Not fun. After I was discharged from the hospital, I still needed skilled nursing care as well as Physical therapy and Occupational therapy.  I was so delighted to find the Remington Club. The staff was professional, gentle, and very kind. They knew what they were doing as they frequently see patients with the same condition as mine. In short order (2 days), they had managed my pain and had me up and walking with the help of the staff and a walker. While it took some time to get me independent, the folk at Remington Club were wonderful and accomplished a lot with this old man.

Dr. Singh was assigned to my case. He is one of the best doctor I have known, and I have seen a lot. He was very knowledgeable, kind and very approachable. He observed my pain level and prescribed the appropriate medication and dosage. There was no nonsense about the pain meds; something unheard of in todayâ€™s medicine!  He was truly wonderful.

Going to Physical / Occupational Therapy was like going to a party. Every member of the therapy staff was wonderful. They knew exactly what exercises would work for me and gently guided me through all the steps. Every person had a plethora of tricks around specific actions like climbing stairs, getting in and out of a car, dressing myself, etc.  Very helpful.

I canâ€™t say enough about how good my experience at Remington Club was despite my injury.  These people are outstanding in all aspects of a post operative rehabilitation facility!</text>

<Resp>None< /Resp><Gmap_id>0x80dbf0d1bc607af9:0xcfc24ed4e6c28a7b</Gmap_id></record></dataset><record>
< Review>
What an incredible community to live in!  I have many great memories of coming to The Remington Club as a kid to volunteer with my elementary school class.  My grandfather moved here when his health began to decline a couple of years ago.  One of the many things I like about The Remington Club is their multi-level care approach.

This allows someone to move into their independent living community and as the level of care required increases, they can accommodate higher levels of care at their assisted-living community.

Additionally, they have a great staff with very low turnover in comparison to the rest of the industry. If you are considering an assisted/independent living community, I highly recommend taking a tour of this one before making a final decision!</Review>

< text>
Kudos to the Remington Club in Rancho Bernardo, California. Management and all team members have worked diligently to make our residence a safe environment during the past year of the Covid-19 pandemic.  Nearly 100% of residents and staff have received the first and second Pfizer vaccines, while sheltering in place. A remarkable percentage!

The disruption of our previous life style has been met with a well planned program in order to meet the needs of everyone involved.  Our appreciation is evident daily, especially when a server brings our evening meal to our door.  One can actually see his/her smile through the facial covering, along with the twinkling eyes.

The review following was written, but not posted, shortly following the celebration of the Remington Club's 30th anniversary and is still "current".

Five Stars to the Remington Club in Rancho Bernardo, California.
Recently I, and about 499 other people, attended the 30th anniversary of the Remington Club.

This event was super special.  Included was a photographer who took pictures of the ladies and gents, a caricaturist who exaggerated the good features of those willing to participate, several couples whose smooth dancing entertained the audience, and there was food aplenty!

The young servers, handsomely dressed in their tuxedos, were scattered among us, offering delicious appetizers throughout various areas of the Campus, indoors and outside by the lovely swimming pool and terrace. area.

At one point in the festivities our Executive Director, Kristen Kearnaghan, welcomed the guests who were assembled in the main lobby and told a bit of the history of the Remington Club in Rancho Bernardo.  She gave special recognition to those residents who have made the Remington Club their home for ten or more years, one having moved here in 1999.  The Management team and all the staff worked tirelessly, making the 30th anniversary an afternoon to remember.  Each guest was given a souvenir glass,  commemorating the occasion, along with a copy of the 30th anniversary edition of Pearls of Wisdom, words to live by, from the residents and staff of the Remington Club. All in all a most enjoyable celebration.</text>

I have to tell you, on the very first day they woke up in their new place at the Remington Club my dad made his way to his motorized wheelchair  (which he previously used less than a handful of times) and he says "well....lets go" and sure enough he made it to the elevator and we all went downstairs and had breakfast (due to his lack of speech and limited words we had him point to the menu) my dad ordered his own food and a cup of coffee. (I filled in the staff and informed them that he is fine "upstairs" but he just cannot fully vocalize his thoughts) they were a great help. yesterday I had a long drive from Los Angeles to San Jose. Unfortunately, I was running late and was worried that I would not make it in on time. However, Michelle (front desk rep) was wonderful and ensured me that she will way for me for 15 minutes after 5:30pm to ensure that I get my unit that day. All other storage unit locations were quick to tell me that they can not help and Michelle did help. I went in and she answered all of my questions and gave me additional information that is important. Over all she was very pleasant and showed that she cares for her customers.

As for the unit, I got a 5x 10 and stored my belongings for a studio apartment. Everything fit in there very well. My bolt recommendation is that you buy moisture control for the unit so your things donâ€™t get moist and stinky (they sell it on property). I unfortunately did not purchase it and went into the unit feeling the moisture. The associate will try to sell it to you on the spot so it would be something to consider.

HAPPY STORING!<//text>

<user>105787430582310677501</user>< Review>
My wife Donna and I use this Public Storage for supplies and inventory for our business, Kadori Gifts.  This place is fantastic for three reasons:

1.  People - Juanita and Paul are absolutely great!  Very friendly, supportive and always accommodating when we need help like borrowing a hand truck.
2.  Location - Its only blocks from our house and has great access to Capital Expressway, Hwy 85 and Hwy 87, so we can easily get anywhere in the bay area.
3.  Facilities - They keep this place neat and clean, just how we like it.

We highly recommend this Public Storage location for anyone who needs some extra space in a clean, well managed location with friendly staff!</Review>

<Time>1394581356808</Time><rate>5<//rate>< text>
It is not at every storage place that one gets both efficiency and friendliness.  Juanita, who works part-time at the 3911 Snell Avenue Public Storage, exhibits both these qualities.  She went the extra mile to arrange the use of a flatbed cart that I could return the next day and showed me all the "ins-and-outs" of the 10 x 10 space and its locking mechanism plus the codes for entering/exiting the premises and for getting into the G Unit.  I appreciated the mixture of professionalism with the ability to share humorous anecdotes about life at the Ps where she works.  When suggestions were made that could improve the service, she was quick to make an appropriate notation.  Juanita's personality combined with "the personal touch" helped make my stay an enjoyable experience.<//text>

< Review>
Finally done w/ this place.

They recently cut back their hours of access and close at 6pm now. Then, raised their rates 20% out of no where (just so happens was 2 months after i moved units to save 20% in monthly fee's), stating they were needed for upkeep (they just repainted the place a month before, seriously?). Both, big red flags for me since this place is nothing amazing.
Unless you never access your storage, or are a flea market vendor, I'd pick another place to store your belongings.

The upside is, the people who work there are really nice.

SO! glad to be out of there.

Ps. Thought I should update this review since I've now been getting calls from the staff saying that anything under a 5star review for this location gets the staff in trouble from their corporate managers. So, here's a 1 star review. This 1 star is not because of the employees (which btw were always helpful and nice), but because of the policies put into place by the higher ups. If it's the truth that district managers come down on property managers for them enforcing your (public storage) changed policies, and ex-customers leaving honest reviews, then I'm even happier I got out of giving this company my money every month.< /Review>

Itâ€™s a popular meeting place for locals in the evenings and on the weekends. During the summer months, the parkâ€™s fountain features a popular splash pad thatâ€™s a big hit with little ones looking to cool off.
